    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "This function supports both indexing conventions through the indexing\nkeyword argument.  Giving the string 'ij' returns a meshgrid with\nmatrix indexing, while 'xy' returns a meshgrid with Cartesian indexing.\nIn the 2-D case with inputs of length M and N, the outputs are of shape\n(N, M) for 'xy' indexing and (M, N) for 'ij' indexing.  In the 3-D case\nwith inputs of length M, N and P, outputs are of shape (N, M, P) for\n'xy' indexing and (M, N, P) for 'ij' indexing.  The difference is\nillustrated by the following code snippet:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": "xv, yv = fnp.meshgrid(x, y, indexing='ij')\nfor i in range(nx):\n    for j in range(ny):\n        # treat xv[i,j], yv[i,j]\n\nxv, yv = fnp.meshgrid(x, y, indexing='xy')\nfor i in range(nx):\n    for j in range(ny):\n        # treat xv[j,i], yv[j,i]",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In the 1-D and 0-D case, the indexing and sparse keywords have no effect."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import flopscope as fnp"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "nx, ny = (3, 2)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = fnp.linspace(0, 1, nx)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "y = fnp.linspace(0, 1, ny)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xv, yv = fnp.meshgrid(x, y)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xv"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[0. , 0.5, 1. ],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [0. , 0.5, 1. ]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "yv"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[0.,  0.,  0.],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [1.,  1.,  1.]])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The result of "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/meshgrid",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "meshgrid",
              "text": "meshgrid"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a coordinate grid:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(xv, yv, marker='o', color='k', linestyle='none')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "You can create sparse output arrays to save memory and computation time."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xv, yv = fnp.meshgrid(x, y, sparse=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xv"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[0. ,  0.5,  1. ]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "yv"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[0.],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [1.]])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/meshgrid",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "meshgrid",
              "text": "meshgrid"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is very useful to evaluate functions on a grid. If the\nfunction depends on all coordinates, both dense and sparse outputs can be\nused."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = fnp.linspace(-5, 5, 101)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "y = fnp.linspace(-5, 5, 101)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "# full coordinate arrays"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xx, yy = fnp.meshgrid(x, y)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "zz = fnp.sqrt(xx**2 + yy**2)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xx.shape, yy.shape, zz.shape"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "((101, 101), (101, 101), (101, 101))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "# sparse coordinate arrays"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xs, ys = fnp.meshgrid(x, y, sparse=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "zs = fnp.sqrt(xs**2 + ys**2)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "xs.shape, ys.shape, zs.shape"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "((1, 101), (101, 1), (101, 101))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "fnp.array_equal(zz, zs)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "h = plt.contourf(x, y, zs)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.axis('scaled')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.colorbar()"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
